The State Capture Inquiry has heard explosive testimony about an IT company's questionable payments to senior ANC officials. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The State Capture Inquiry heard testimony about an IT company's questionable payments to senior ANC officials on Wednesday. Between 2015 and 2017, EOH allegedly made eight payments to former ANC spokesperson and current national executive committee member, Zizi Kodwa. LIVESTREAM: State capture inquiry to hear money flows related evidence These payments allegedly totalled R375,000. The company also allegedly paid current Johannesburg Mayor, Geoff Makhubo, Reggie Nkabinde from the ANC Youth League and Siyabulela Sintwa, a former personal assistant to Jacob Zuma. The commission heard the details from Steven Powell, Managing Director at ENS Forensics. EOH employed him last year to audit irregular cash flow. READ:Â WATCH: State Capture Inquiry hears Denel testimony Powell told commission Chair, Raymond Zondo, that the payments were reported to the Hawks. Watch the video above for more details on this story.